window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>William Kent Krueger is the award-winning author of the popular Cork O’Connor mysteries. In <i>Purgatory Ridge</i>, Krueger crafts a riveting tale that has ex-sheriff O’Connor on the case after a heated town debate turns deadly. </p> <p>The local Anishinaabe Indian tribe is furious to discover that Karl Lindstrom’s lumber mill is after a grove of trees sacred to tribal lore. So when the mill gets bombed, killing a man, the tribe is blamed. But O’Connor has a different theory.</p>"; 
